description: Thailand's lower house on Friday passed a 3.48 trillion baht ($95.6 billion) budget bill for the 2024 fiscal year, aimed at reviving aimed at reviving Southeast Asia's second-largest economy.
title: Thai parliament passes delayed $96 bln budget for 2024 fiscal year

description: Republican presidential candidate Donald Trump has made a series of inflammatory and racist statements on the U.S. campaign trail since declaring his candidacy in November 2022.
title: Trump’s ‘bloodbath’ and other rhetoric inflame his 2024 campaign trail

description: Poland's Prime Minister Donald Tusk hit his first 100 days in office on Friday with solid public support but facing criticism for failing to meet a host of election promises.
title: After 100 days, Poland's Tusk faces questions over election promises

description: Tourists arriving at Barcelona's airport or gazing at its iconic Sagrada Familia basilica will this Easter holiday be met with large signs in English that read: "Drought alert. During your stay, save water".
title: Ahead of Easter rush, officials say drought must not put off Barcelona tourists

description: Attackers set fire to shops, cars and utility poles in at least 40 locations across Thailand's deep south in the early hours of Friday, authorities said, killing at least one person in a coordinated wave of arson.
title: At least 40 fires set in night of arson across Thailand's south

description: Australia and Britain said in a joint statement on Friday there were potentially devastating consequences of an Israeli ground invasion of Rafah in Gaza.
title: Australia, Britain warn of potentially devastating consequences of Israeli operation in Rafah

description: U.S. Secretary of State of State Antony Blinken shook hands and chatted on Friday with demonstrators in Tel Aviv demanding Israel focus on the release of hostages held by Hamas, promising them that he was working to bring them home.
title: Blinken greets protesters in Israel demanding return of Gaza hostages

description: U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken said on Friday that an offensive on the southern Gaza city of Rafah would risk "further isolating" Israel and damage its long-term security.
title: Blinken says Rafah offensive risks further isolating Israel globally

description: British Foreign Secretary David Cameron said on Friday the UK would work with whomever becomes U.S. president in November, when asked whether the election of Donald Trump would endanger the AUKUS military alliance.
title: British foreign secretary says UK will work with whomever is US president on AUKUS

description: Canada plans to reduce its temporary residents and set a cap on temporary immigration for the first time ever, Immigration Minister Marc Miller said on Thursday, the latest government effort to address a housing shortage and stretched essential services.
title: Canada plans to reduce temporary residents, cap future intake

description: "This is really a battle between good and evil," evangelical TV preacher Hank Kunneman says of the slew of criminal charges facing Donald Trump. "There's something on President Trump that the enemy fears: It's called the anointing."
title: Christian TV evangelicals fire up Trump support with messianic message

description: The European Union Council on Friday decided to impose sanctions on 33 individuals and two entities linked to the death of late Russian opposition leader Alexei Navalny.
title: EU sanctions 33 people over Navalny death

description: Salzburg, the home of Mozart and "The Sound of Music", is not a place known for radical change.
title: Exasperated by cost of housing, Salzburg could elect a Communist mayor

description: Finland will resume funding to the U.N. Palestinian refugee agency UNRWA, its foreign trade and development minister said on Friday.
title: Finland to resume funding to UNRWA

description: A 63-year-old man whom police in South Africa on Thursday said apparently died by suicide was identified by local media as former Steinhoff chief executive Markus Jooste.
title: Former Steinhoff CEO Markus Jooste dies by suicide, reports say

description: At least 40 people were killed and over 100 hurt when gunmen in camouflage clothing opened fire with automatic weapons on people at a concert in the Crocus City Hall near Moscow on Friday, Russia's FSB security service said.
title: Gunmen kill 40 in attack at concert near Moscow, over 100 injured, Russia says

description: Dozens of members of the opposition Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) were detained by police in New Delhi on Friday as they gathered in protest against the arrest of their leader for graft, weeks before India holds general elections.
title: India opposition members detained after arrest of Delhi leader Kejriwal

description: Israeli Finance Minister Bezalel Smotrich on Friday declared 800 hectares in the occupied West Bank as state land, in a move that will facilitate the use of the ground for settlement building.
title: Israel approves new parcel of West Bank land for settlement

description: Israeli forces have detained hundreds of Hamas and Islamic Jihad fighters including a number of security officials and military commanders during its extended raid into Gaza's main hospital, the military's main spokesperson said.
title: Israeli military says troops captured hundreds of fighters in Gaza hospital

description: Kate, Britain's Princess of Wales, said on Friday she was undergoing preventative chemotherapy after tests taken after she had major abdominal surgery in January revealed that cancer had been present.
title: Kate, Princess of Wales, says she has cancer

description: Britain's King Charles, Prince Harry and political leaders offered support to Kate, Princess of Wales, after she said tests following abdominal surgery showed cancer had been present and she was undergoing preventative chemotherapy.
title: King Charles, Prince Harry, politicians offer support to Kate after cancer announcement

description: Britain's King Charles is proud of Kate, Princess of Wales, for her courage in speaking about her treatment after it was discovered cancer had been present following her recent operation, Buckingham Palace said on Friday.
title: King Charles 'so proud' of Kate for speaking about cancer discovery

description: Russia regards itself to be at war due to the West's intervention on Ukraine's side and cannot allow a state to exist on its borders that has shown itself ready to use any method to seize control of Crimea, the Kremlin said on Friday.
title: Kremlin says Russia is at war due to Western intervention on Ukrainian side

description: Lebanon will file an urgent complaint with the U.N. Security Council over what it called Israel's violation of its sovereignty by disrupting its navigation systems, the foreign ministry said on Friday.
title: Lebanon to complain to UN, saying Israel disrupts navigation systems

description: A magnitude 6.1 earthquake struck off the shore of Indonesia's Java island on Friday, at a depth of 10km (6.21 miles), Indonesia's geophysics agency (BKMG) said.
title: Magnitude 6.1 quake strikes off Indonesia's Java island, geophysics agency says

description: At least 40 people were killed and more than 100 injured when gunmen dressed in camouflage opened fire with automatic weapons at a concert hall near Moscow in one of the worst such attacks in Russia in recent years.
title: Major attacks inside Russia

description: Mexico has signed an agreement with Venezuela to deport migrants and reached deals with Mexican and Venezuelan companies to employ them, Foreign Minister Alicia Barcena told a news conference on Thursday.
title: Mexico reaches agreement with Venezuela to deport migrants

description: Moldova's Parliament on Thursday endorsed an appeal to press on with a drive to join the European Union, but the opposition walked out of the vote and separatists in the Transdniestria region urged authorities to drop their claim to the enclave.
title: Moldovan Parliament backs bid to join EU, but divisions remain

description: Montenegro's top court on Friday decided to delay the extradition of Terraform Labs co-founder Do Kwon to South Korea until it clarifies prosecution complaints about the legality of its extradition ruling, the court said on its website.
title: Montenegro court delays extradition of Terraform Labs co-founder to South Korea

description: More than 70 Rohingya are "presumed dead or missing" after a boat they were on capsized off the coast of Indonesia's Aceh province, while 75 have been rescued, the UNHCR refugee agency said on Friday.
title: Over 70 Rohingya dead or missing after boat capsizes off Indonesia's Aceh

description: Pakistan will discuss an Extended Fund Facility (EFF) with the International Monetary Fund (IMF) in Washington next month, Finance Minister Muhammad Aurangzeb said on Friday, as the country looks to alleviate a full-scale economic crisis.
title: Pakistan to discuss Extended Fund Facility with IMF next month, says finance minister

description: William Franklin, recently released after serving 44 years in prison, could walk from a Philadelphia courtroom an exonerated man on Friday, or he may face another trial for a 1976 murder he says he did not commit.
title: Philadelphia man released after 44 years in prison may face new trial

description: The U.S. military will not be involved in development of a port in the Philippines' remote northernmost islands near Taiwan, the local governor said on Friday, removing a potential source of friction with China over the U.S. presence in the region.
title: Philippines to build new islands port near Taiwan without U.S. help, governor says

description: In India, the world's most populous democracy, elections mean millions of voters boasting a forefinger daubed in purple, and a factory in the southern city of Mysuru is the source of all of the nation's indelible ink.
title: Purple fingers and indelible ink are the hallmarks of India's elections

description: Russia has added what it calls the "LGBT movement" to a list of extremist and terrorist organisations, state media said on Friday.
title: Russia adds 'LGBT movement' to list of extremist and terrorist organisations

description: Russia said on Friday that if the United States knew for sure that Ukraine was not involved in a mass shooting incident at a concert hall near Moscow Washington should share any information it had.
title: Russia says United States must share any information it has on attack near Moscow

description: Russia and Ukraine believe that their crisis will be solved through talks, even as both are adamant on their positions and have huge differences when it comes to peace talks, China's special envoy for Eurasian affairs said on Friday.
title: Russia, Ukraine see crisis eventually resolved through talks, China's special envoy says

description: Russia's newly appointed ambassador to Japan has warned Tokyo of serious consequences and retaliatory steps if Patriot missile systems manufactured under U.S. licence in Japan end up in Ukraine, the RIA news agency reported on Friday.
title: Russia warns Japan of 'serious consequences' if Patriot missiles made there end up in Ukraine - RIA

description: The Kremlin on Friday said Western banks' legal departments understand the "catastrophic consequences" that would follow should the EU proceed with plans to confiscate Russian assets.
title: Russia warns Western banks of catastrophic consequences over asset confiscation

description: About 15 blasts were heard in Ukraine's Kharkiv on Friday morning, mayor Ihor Terekhov said, and Russian missile strikes appeared to be targeting the city's power supply, causing partial blackouts.
title: Russian missile strikes damage power supply in Ukraine's Kharkiv

description: Spain has agreed with the leaders of Ireland, Malta and Slovenia to take the first steps towards recognising a Palestinian state, Prime Minister Pedro Sanchez said on Friday following a meeting of the European Council in Brussels.
title: Spain, Ireland, Malta, Slovenia agree to work towards Palestinian state recognition

description: The former chief executive of South African multinational retailer Steinhoff had been notified of an arrest warrant against him shortly before he was found dead in what local media called a suicide, the elite Hawks police unit said on Friday.
title: Steinhoff ex-CEO had expected arrest before being found near death, police say

description: On an overcast day in Tokyo this week, three dozen men and women strolled through a botanical garden in groups of four, making awkward conversation as they searched for clues to a mystery-solving game - and a potential partner for life.
title: Tokyo, Tokyo, make me a match! Metropolis hopes AI app will spur marriages

description: China interrupted an attempt by several non-governmental groups on Friday to pay homage to a late Chinese human rights activist in a tense incident at a U.N. rights body that exposed divisions between Western countries and supporters of Beijing.
title: Tribute to deceased Chinese dissident exposes fractures at UN rights body

description: Prime Minister Justin Trudeau's Liberal government on Thursday survived a no-confidence motion brought by the opposition Conservative Party over Canada's carbon tax, which looks set to be a major issue in an election likely to be held next year.
title: Trudeau government survives no confidence vote over Canada carbon tax rise

description: Kate, Britain's Princess of Wales, said on Friday that tests taken after a surgery she had in January had revealed cancer had been present and she was now undergoing a course of preventative chemotherapy.
title: UK royal Kate's statement about cancer discovery

description: A Ukrainian deputy prime minister said on Friday Russian oil refineries were legitimate targets for its forces, after a media report said the United States, a close ally, had asked Kyiv to stop conducting drone strikes on refineries.
title: Ukraine says Russian oil refineries are legitimate targets

description: Ukraine's state hydropower company said on Friday a Russian strike hit Ukraine's largest dam, the DniproHES in Zaporizhzhia, but that there was no risk of a breach, while power infrastructure in other regions was also hit, officials said.
title: Ukraine says Russian strike hit Ukraine's largest dam during mass strike on energy infrastructure

description: Ukraine will scrap its "sponsors of war" blacklist, the centrepiece of its campaign to pressure companies doing business in Russia, on Friday, after a backlash from countries from to Austria to China, two people familiar with the matter said.
title: Ukraine to drop Russia business blacklist after backlash

description: The United Nations Security Council on Friday failed to pass a resolution calling for an immediate ceasefire in Gaza as part of a hostage deal after Russia and China vetoed the measure proposed by the United States.
title: UN Security Council fails to pass US resolution calling for immediate ceasefire in Gaza

description: The United States has urged Ukraine to halt strikes on Russian energy infrastructure, warning that drone strikes risk provoking retaliation and driving up global oil prices, the Financial Times reported on Friday, citing people familiar with the matter.
title: US has urged Ukraine to halt strikes on Russian energy infrastructure, FT reports

description: The United States on Friday imposed sanctions on 15 Sinaloa Cartel members and six Mexico-based entities involved in the illicit manufacture and trafficking of fentanyl and other deadly drugs, Deputy Treasury Secretary Wally Adeyemo announced.
title: US levies fentanyl-related sanctions on Sinaloa members, Mexico-based entities

description: The U.S. military on Thursday said it had destroyed two anti-ship ballistic missiles and an unmanned surface vessel launched by Houthis from Yemen.
title: US military says it destroyed ballistic missiles launched by Houthis

description: Israel's spy chief was due to travel to Qatar on Friday for ceasefire negotiations while the U.S. planned to put a resolution calling for an immediate truce in Gaza to a vote of the U.N. Security Council, intensifying pressure on its ally.
title: US puts pressure on Israel with Gaza ceasefire resolution as Qatar talks continue

description: Russian news agencies reported multiple casualties after a shooting incident at a concert venue near Moscow on Friday.
title: What we know about the shooting at a concert venue near Moscow

description: The International Court of Justice (ICJ) will hear objections by Azerbaijan against Armenia's case accusing Baku of violating a U.N. anti-discrimination treaty in public sittings on April 15 to April 19, it said in a press release on Friday.
title: World Court to hear Azerbaijan objection to Armenia discrimination case
